For 20 years, we have been committed to providing safe access to high-quality medical marijuana for all of our patients.

We have a large variety of THC, CBD, CBN  products ranging from, 2.5-20-50mg pills, and/or raw product. Our products have natural cannabis terpenes which enhance the medical benefits via the entourage effect. Those who wish a more balanced THC/CBD/CBN profile in your medication can add whichever of our THC products is most appropriate. A full list and pictures coming soon as we are just getting started in online market.

We offer only PREMIUM-quality buds grown organically with love by local and international growers.

 

ORDER ONLINE @ WWW.CANNAMEDICS.CA

listings.name: Bud Lab
listings.intro_body:
Your #1 Canadian Cannabis Resource

BudLab.ca ships medical marijuana products across Canada, to any location, with quick and friendly service. We are constantly updating our inventory so check out our site to make sure you are seeing the latest deals and offerings.

 

As a cannabis enthusiast, Bud is always working and shopping around to assure that he is offering the highest quality, most affordable, most healthful products on the market. In recent years, he has become very frustrated about the public attacks on the smoking and consumption of cannabis, when in-reality he knows the incredible health benefits it can provide. His goal is to destroy the stigmas and myths around the utilization of marijuana products. Join Bud and help vaporize the myths about the usage of marijuana!

listings.name: House Of Weeds
listings.intro_body:
Our Requirements 

We will require your government issued identification, be at least 19 years of age in most provinces, 18+ in Quebec and 18+ Alberta.

Once we have confirmed your age we will fulfill your order and ship immediately.

How to Order

Take a look through our extensive menu. Once you have found products you like, hit the checkout button and fill out you're information.

 

All e-transfer payments will be made to houseofweeds@outlook.com. 

 

Please include your invoice/order number in the payment notes.
